Bar Rescue is an American television show that premiered on Spike TV on July 17, 2011. It stars Jon Taffer, a nightclub consultant, who offers his services to failing bars in hopes of turning their fortunes around. It was renewed on September 14, 2011 for a second season which will air in the summer of 2012.

Bars mean money, but they also mean stress if they aren't properly run. Jon Taffer is a bar and nightclub owner who has started, flipped, or owned over 600 bars and clubs in his career and currently owns one of the most highly respected consulting firms in the bar and nightclub industry. On the show he travels around the country employing his expertise to return struggling bars to the cash cows they once were. Everything from the science of the perfect pour, to the height of the bar stools is a key factor in making a bar the hottest place in town.
